All 12 modules have 100\% documentation coverage at Tiers 1--2
(\texttt{AGENTS.md}, \texttt{README.md}); the 10 active subpackages
additionally carry \texttt{SKILL.md} for Tier-3 agentic skill discovery.
This places \texttt{template/} among the first research software
frameworks to implement an MCP-aligned skill layer
{[}@anthropic2024mcp{]} across its infrastructure stack.
\end{block}

\begin{block}{Agentic Skill Documentation Coverage}
\protect\phantomsection\label{agentic-skill-documentation-coverage}
The three-tier
\hyperlink{documentation-duality-and-the-agentic-skill-architecture}{skill
protocol} achieves complete coverage across all infrastructure modules:

{\def\LTcaptype{none} % do not increment counter
\begin{longtable}[]{@{}lcc@{}}
\toprule\noalign{}
Documentation Layer & Files & Coverage \\
\midrule\noalign{}
\endhead
System (\texttt{CLAUDE.md}) & 1 & 100\% \\
Structural (\texttt{AGENTS.md}) & 12+ per-directory & 100\% \\
Skill (\texttt{SKILL.md}) & 12 modules & 100\% \\
PAI (\texttt{PAI.md}) & 1 (infrastructure-level) & --- \\
Human (\texttt{README.md}) & 12+ per-directory & 100\% \\
\bottomrule\noalign{}
\end{longtable}
}

This four-layer coverage creates 12 fully described, MCP-mappable tool
endpoints that a sufficiently capable agent could invoke without any
source-code access. The aggregate documentation footprint (147+ files)
represents a deliberate engineering investment: each documentation file
is not commentary but a specification, enforcing architectural
constraints through structured natural language {[}@lau2025aicoding{]}.
\end{block}

